# I successfully harvested more wood and now have a total of 22 wood in my inventory. 
# Next, I will gather some stone to diversify my resources, which will allow me to craft additional items.

# I will find the nearest stone resource and harvest some stone.

stone_resource_position = nearest(Resource.Stone)  # Finding the nearest stone resource
move_to(stone_resource_position)  # Moving to the nearest stone resource position
harvest_resource(stone_resource_position, quantity=10)  # Harvesting 10 stone from the specified position

# Check the inventory after harvesting stone
print(f"Inventory changed to {inspect_inventory()}")  # Inspecting the updated inventory again
